1) GitHub login

2) Repository - A locatin where we update our source code in txt format.

3) Git init
   init is nothing but a initializing.

4) git status

   show the files under the staging area and working area.
   Whatever we can see in red colour that is in working area where
   as green colour shows staging area.

5) git add .
   OR
   git add select_file1 select_file2

   It will add the files from working area to staging area.

6) git commit -m "basic concept for git learner"
   -m is nothing but a message

7) git remote add origin url_repository
   It is nothing but gives direction or location
   where we want to send or store.

8) git remote -v
   check the remote origin added or not
